==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Teachable
<hw>Teach"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of being
taught; apt to learn; also, willing to receive instruction;
docile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We ought to bring our minds free, unbiased, and
<qex>teachable</qex>, to learn our religion from the Word of God.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Teachableness</ent>⟦br⟧
